    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Escaping CDATA]]></title>
    <link href="http://dcadenas.github.com/blog/2007/11/13/escaping/"/>
    <updated>2007-11-13T23:13:00-02:00</updated>
    <id>http://dcadenas.github.com/blog/2007/11/13/escaping</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>This is a handy code that wraps a string with CDATA escaping any CDATA inside it:</p>

<p>```c#
public static string CData(string data)
{</p>

<pre><code>if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(data))
{
    return string.Empty;
}

string result = Regex.Replace(data, "]]&gt;", "]]]]&gt;&lt;![CDATA[&gt;");
return "&lt;![CDATA[" + result + "]]&gt;";
</code></pre>

<p>}
```</p>
